<section class="banner-section-service"></section>
<section class="container px-4 py-5">
    <div class="row p-4 pb-0 pe-lg-0 pt-lg-5 align-items-center">
        <div class="col-lg-7 text-center text-lg-start ">
            <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold lh-1 mb-3 ">VAT Registeration Services in Dubai,UAE</h1>
            <nav aria-label="breadcrumb" class="breadcrumb-text">
                <ol class="breadcrumb">
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a asp-action="Index" asp-controller="Home">Home</a> /</li>
                    <li class="breadcrumb-item active" aria-current="page">VAT Registeration Services in Dubai,UAE</li>
                </ol>
            </nav>
            <hr class="my-4">
            <h2>Register Your Company VAT Number in Dubai - All You Need to Know</h2>
            <p class="col-lg-10 fs-4">
                Value Added Tax (VAT) is a tax that is levied on the value added to goods and services during the production process. In the UAE, VAT was introduced on January 1, 2018, and is currently levied at a rate of 5%. As a business owner, 
                it is important to understand the requirements for VAT registration and how it will impact your business operations.
            </p>
          
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-10 mx-auto col-lg-5 pb-3  ">
            <img src="/assets/images/services/ser-3.webp" alt="Accounting Firm in Dubai" class="img-fluid rounded-3 mb-3 ">
            @await Html.PartialAsync("_AsideContact")
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="service-section py-10">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row gx-5 gy-30">
            <div class="col-lg-9">
                <div class="row gx-5 px-3  pb-30 mb-5">
                    <div class="mb-60 mt-5">
                        <h4 class="text-underline body-font fw-bold fs-4 mb-30 pb-20">Who is Required to Register for VAT?</h4>
                        <p>
                            All businesses that have a taxable supply of goods and services in the UAE are required to register
                            for VAT if their taxable supplies and imports exceed the mandatory registration threshold of <b>AED 375,000</b> .
                            This threshold applies to businesses operating in all Emirates of the UAE, including Abu Dhabi, Dubai, Sharjah, and others.
                        </p>
                       

                    </div>
                    <div class="mb-2 mt-2">
                        <h4 class="text-underline body-font fw-bold fs-4 mb-30 pb-20">What is the VAT Registration Process?</h4>
                        <p>
                            The VAT registration process in the UAE is straightforward and can be completed online through the Federal Tax Authority (FTA) website.
                            To register for VAT, you will need to provide the following information:
                            <ul>
                                <li>Business name and trade license number</li>
                                <li>Contact details for the business, including the address and telephone number</li>
                                <li>Information about the business owner(s), including their passport information</li>
                                <li>Details about the business’s taxable supplies and imports</li>
                                <li>A valid email address for the business</li>


                            </ul>
                        </p>


                    </div>
                    <section class="service-section">
                        <div class="container pt-2 pb-2 ">
                            <div class="service-offer bg-light py-30 pe-40 mb-5">
                                <h2>Let Experts Accounting & Tax Consultancy Help with VAT Registration</h2>
                                <p class="">
                                    By choosing Experts Accounting & Tax Consultancy for your VAT registration needs, you can benefit from:
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>A streamlined and efficient VAT registration process</li>
                                        <li>Expert guidance on all VAT-related requirements</li>
                                        <li>A dedicated team of accountants and tax specialists available to answer your questions and provide ongoing support</li>
                                    </ul>
                                </p>
                                <a onclick="return gtag_report_conversion('tel:+971585397170');" href="tel:+971585397170" class="btn btn-lg btn-success">Let’s Work Together<i class="icon-arrows-slim-right ps-2"></i></a>

                            </div>
                            @* #FFD700;*@
                        </div>

                    </section>
                </div>
      
                <div class="mb-60 mt-5">
                    <h4 class="text-underline body-font fw-bold fs-4 mb-30 pb-20">Penalties for Not Registering for VAT</h4>
                    <p>
                        Failing to register for VAT when required can result in significant penalties, including fines and possible imprisonment.
                        In addition, unregistered businesses may also face reputational damage and a loss of credibility with customers and suppliers.
                    </p>


                </div>
            </div>
